Full Description: Rollr is the simplest and most professional way to publish content on the web.   Founded in Tampa, FL, Rollr was created as a tool for the average person to have a presence on the web.  Rollr is technically a blog tool, but it also bridges the gap between blogging and social networks.  With Rollr a user can post long detailed articles, quick status updates, great looking photos, and more.  All of this gets posted to a completely personalized, professional looking webpage free from branding, ads, and other annoyances.   Another important feature of Rollr is how easily it integrates with Facebook and Twitter.  All posts are optionally shared to the user's Facebook feed and tweeted to their followers. Finally, in order to post frequently and easily, Rollr came out with a very simple mobile application.  The application is available for both Android and iPhone, and it ensures that the users are able to update their websites easily.   Right now, development is done in San Pedro Sula, Honduras as the co-founder/developer lives there.  One of Rollr's goals is to be able to produce an influential and profitable company that can help sustain missionary work in Honduras and other parts of the world.

Description: Thrasio for Ad agencies. Webphore is tech-enabled ad agency for small businesses.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Webphore is a revolutionary startup that aims to bridge the gap between small and medium-sized businesses (SMBs) and effective marketing solutions. Recognizing the challenges faced by SMBs in finding affordable and efficient ad agencies, Webphore has developed a game-changing approach. By leveraging the Thrasio model for ad agencies, Webphore acquires and enhances small and regional agencies, empowering them with advanced technology and streamlined operations. This enables these agencies to serve a larger customer base with reduced staff, giving them the ability to compete with big agencies.
